group_1.narration: <Hanna's Side>

group_1.textCenter: Insolent brat!@You bring shame to your family!

group_1.narration: My father threw me out on the balcony in my@underwear, leaving me shivering and trembling…
I heard a Christmas song playing somewhere@and realized that today was the big day…@A Christmas from hell.
I thought I felt a presence behind me,@but it was my mother looking on@sadly from inside that warm room.
Just when I was about to ask for help…
She turned away and hurried@to the back of the room.
In that moment, I felt intensely that I didn't@want to be like that…like my mother.
That's right. I wasn't going to be someone@who turned a blind eye to things.@If there was someone in need,@I'd reach out to help.@Then surely, the world would be—

group_1.textLeft: Wh-what're you doing?!

group_1.textRight: You guys are the ones trying to gang up and@bully someone who's all alone.

group_1.textLeft: Tch…

group_1.textRight: What's wrong? Your shoes are falling apart?@Can't afford to get new ones at the orphanage?

group_1.textLeft: You did this…?@You're trying to get back at me!

group_1.textRight: Oops, sor-ryyy!@I accidentally ripped up your gym clothes!

group_1.textLeft: Wha…?!
Come on…let's go.

group_1.textRight: …And now I tore your textbook to shreds, too.

group_1.textLeft: Even you…

group_1.narration: From that day forward,@I became the center of bullying.
They acted like their bullying was justified@by bringing up my origins, but there@isn't any justifying what they did.
And yet…no one was open to my perspective,@not even the student I saved…

group_1.textLeft: ...There're some shits at school who really@piss me off.
I want you to...make 'em disappear!

group_1.textRight: Disappear?

group_1.textLeft: Yeah, erase them from this world!

group_1.narration: That's why I made that wish.
I was no longer qualified to save people@like the heroes on TV… If anything,@I'm the sort who gets defeated by them.
I'm such a…

group_1.textCenter: I want my dear friend to be alive!@That's all I want…!

group_1.narration: If there's someone who needs me@and calls me her dear friend…

group_1.textLeft: …I'm scared…@I'm scared, Hanna…

group_1.textRight: (...Sena…)

group_1.narration: If someone is asking me for help…
Even if I'm powerless,@I want to be on their side.
Even if it kills me,@I won't turn a blind eye to them.
Sena is selfish.@She told me not to leave her alone,@but she does just the same to me@without a care in the world.
My manager gave me a Christmas cake, so I was@setting up an early party for the two of us…
But…if Sena wants to do something,@there's nothing I can say against her.@I don't have the right.

group_1.textCenter: …Even if it's my fault that she has to go@on this journey with me.

group_1.narration: Right… She's taking me on this path@towards ruin in order to protect me.@The reason she had to run is because of me…
Just who do I think I am@to want to be on her side?@I'm a coward who's just taking advantage@of her purity and kindness…
But…

group_1.textCenter: Sena… Being alone is so lonely…@*Sniff…* *Sob…*

group_1.narration: With Sena, it feels like every day is shining,@no matter what it is. Where I used to feel dread,@I can find a glimmer of hope for tomorrow.
I'm sorry, Sena…@I feel like I'm no good without you…@So don't leave me…@Stay next to me and smile.

group_1.textRight: Breaking news! This report just came in…
…A man was found lying on a street in the city,@unconscious and in critical condition…

group_1.textCenter: That's in this town…?@The same thing happened again…

group_1.narration: Sena will be fine…@Her body is different from normal people…@Even if that incident was the work of@some serial attacker… She'll be fine…@She'll be fine…!
…But why does my heart feel so uneasy?

group_1.textRight: *Gasp*
Y-you…
…You're telling me to follow?
Ah, w-wait a sec! @Where are you going?!

group_1.narration: I felt something was off as soon@as I stepped on that floor.
Something was stirring in the darkness…@I heard a broken voice cutting up from below.@My instincts were screaming at me@to stop in my tracks and turn back.

group_1.textRight: Sena! Is Sena safe?!@If you did anything to her…

group_1.narration: Sena was standing in the corner@next to all the stationery supplies,@her whole body was bathed@in something dark and sticky.
I understood then that Sena hadn't been@subjected to anything by these Familiars…

group_1.textRight: S-Sena…

group_1.textLeft: Oh… Is that you, Hanna?
That's funny…@I didn't recognize you for a moment.
I was going to write your name on my arm…@That way I wouldn't forget it.

group_1.textRight: Writing my name…?

group_1.textLeft: Yeah. Here, take a look.

group_1.textRight: Is that…a pen?

group_1.textLeft: I was actually trying to find the matching pen@to give you as a gift.
But…no matter how hard I looked, all I could@find was this fake thing…
It has a crescent moon charm instead of a star.@It's a fake copy.

group_1.textRight: …For me? You were doing this for me?

group_1.textLeft: Yes! I wanted to make you happy, Hanna!

group_1.narration: Everything before me turned pitch-black…@Sena has crossed a line she can't go@back on and has become an enemy@of this town… No, the whole world…
Sena must've been responsible@for that series of incidents that have@been happening everywhere we go…@I should've connected the dots earlier.
What do I do? Take Sena to the police…?@No, they don't have a chance of stopping her.
Sena will never again be the same now@that she's like this… I pushed her too hard,@even though she had such little magic…@This is why she's been acting so strange.
…There's nothing I can do, is there?@Since her magic is dwindling, she'll probably@keep getting even weirder and make the@same mistakes over and over…
The only way to stop her is to end her.
…I wasn't going to let Sena die.@If we got caught by those girls chasing us,@I was determined to die alone,@but…in this case…I can't…

group_1.textRight: Sena…don't feel lonely.@I'll follow you soon.

group_1.textLeft: You want to play tag?@[chara:114401:lipSynch_0][wait:0.8][chara:114401:lipSynch_1][chara:114401:cheek_0][chara:114401:face_mtn_ex_010.exp3.json]But I need to find your pen first!
I want you to have a happy Christmas too.

group_1.narration: "I don't want Hanna to say that she doesn't@have any good memories anymore."

group_1.textLeft: I'm going to rewrite all of your bad memories…

group_1.textRight: …Why would you go so far…?

group_1.textLeft: Because you're my hero!

group_1.narration: Ahh… Why is this happening?
Ever since I erased those bullies with my wish,@deep down, I've always regretted it…@Even though I died once to deny myself and@reject this world smeared with malice…
I…I actually believe in justice.@Up until I made my wish, I believed that if@I could become someone who could prove there@was justice, even I could love this shitty world.
So right here, right now, I'm putting@an end to that unfulfilled dream.
I'm…only on Sena's side.

group_1.textRight: Sena…

group_1.textLeft: …Hey, Hanna.

group_1.textRight: I'll be who I want to be.
Because that's probably what it means to be@a Magical Girl.
…Although I'm an Uwasa now.

group_1.textLeft: What do you mean?@This is so beyond me, I don't understand.

group_1.textRight: …I'm going to protect you, Sena.

group_1.narration: Yes, even if I don't remember@a single thing about you.

group_1.textRight: …Aren't your hands cold?@Lemme warm you up.

group_1.textLeft: Erm… I-is that really okay? [chara:114401:lipSynch_0][wait:0.8][chara:114401:lipSynch_1][chara:114401:cheek_0][chara:114401:face_mtn_ex_030.exp3.json]But I was playing@in the sand, so my hands are so dirty…

group_1.textRight: Heh? You were playing in the sand?

group_1.textLeft: That's right! A pile of sand came crashing down,@and that's how I found this pen.

group_1.textRight: I see…@Your hands are clean though, Sena.
It doesn't matter what anyone says.@They look beautiful to me…

group_1.narration: Even if I can't remember anything about Sena,@I've decided to be perfectly evil for her sake.
